cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on visual localization for autonomous driving, which falls under the intersection of computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel Monte Carlo localization algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper uses image retrieval and encoding techniques, which are common in the fields of machine learning and computer graphics, making cs.LG and cs.GR possible sub-categories.
